    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="494"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 800.115/880</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at London</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SRP1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-21">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Every insurance company in London and Liverpool and member of Lloyd’s agrees to
                    insert clause excluding risk liability from any claim arising from capture or
                    detention of ship by British Government or allies. Refusal under government
                    insurance scheme to permit camperdown to proceed Denmark and seizure of <hi
                        rend="italic">Platuria</hi> [?] to-day bound for Aarhus, indicate increasing
                    disposition to prevent shipments grains, foodstuffs, oil, and copper to
                    Scandinavia.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SRP1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Skinner</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
